Third-party content notices.

The validation corpus and worked-examples collection bundle verbatim
content from third parties under the following postures:

  - AI-generated content. Bundled corpus and worked-example assets
    include verbatim outputs from third-party AI providers (Anthropic
    Claude, OpenAI GPT, Google Gemini, xAI Grok). These outputs are
    redistributed in service of the methodology's transparency
    discipline (showing the documents Frame Check was measured on).
    Each provider's terms of service govern downstream redistribution
    of model outputs; consult the relevant provider's terms before
    redistributing the LLM-generated portions of the bundled assets.
    Locations of AI-generated content:
    - data/worked_examples/four-llms-on-bitcoin-retirement-2026/llm_responses.json
    - data/worked_examples/ai-on-life-decisions-startup-2026/data.json
      (response_text from GPT-5)
    - data/worked_examples/divergence-on-claude-bitcoin-retirement-2026/source_document.md
      and divergence_output.json (response from Anthropic Claude)
    - data/worked_examples/grok-on-nvidia-earnings-2026/data.json
      (llm_summary from xAI Grok; the file also bundles the NVIDIA
      press release source under source.text, governed by the
      press-release posture below)
    - The eight derived corpus entries under
      validation/decision_readiness/corpus/four-llms-{bitcoin,startup}-{claude,gemini,grok,openai}/

  - Press release content. The validation corpus and worked-examples
    bundle verbatim third-party press releases for transparency:
    - NVIDIA Q4 FY24 earnings (also bundled in
      data/worked_examples/grok-on-nvidia-earnings-2026/data.json
      under source.text, plus
      validation/decision_readiness/corpus/nvidia-q4-fy24-press-release/document.md).
      Copyright remains with NVIDIA Corporation.
    Press release content is redistributed under standard fair-use
    posture for analytical excerpting in research and methodology
